- 'Strong chance of weathering the storm' refers to the probability of controlling the outbreak being greater than 0.5;
- 'New confirmed cases by infection date' is a specific metric used in the query.

- The probability values are used to assess the likelihood of controlling the outbreak;
- An alert is triggered when the number of new cases exceeds a specified threshold;
- The highest probability indicates the region with the best control measures.

- 'High confidence level' indicates a high degree of reliability in the estimation;
- 'Median of new confirmed cases' refers to the middle value in the distribution of new confirmed cases;
- 'Top 3 regions' are the regions with the highest median values of new confirmed cases.

